%BOM---------------------
Date:10/7/2008 3:00:26 AM
From:Don Earl
Didn't Buffet load up on physical gold sometime back?

How about gold as a value play? Wouldn't turning fiat dollars into something
with real worth, be the ultimate value play?

Consider this: Around the turn of the last century, a dollar was worth just shy
of an ounce of gold. By 1934 a dollar was worth 1/20th an ounce of gold. Today
a dollar is worth 1/860th an ounce of gold. If that trend continues, in another
century, an ounce of gold will be worth over $700,000.

Of course if you told someone in 1908 that in one hundred years an ounce of
gold would cost a thousand dollars, they would have told you you were crazy.
