selling.

I have never seen so much selling with such a buyer's strike. I do know from
the phone calls I have been getting, there will be lots of margin calls and
forced selling tomorrow morning. A lot of the good stocks were being sold today
to raise capital. This includes most of the consolidated oil companies.

The value investor likes to pick up companies that other people are forced to
sell that are significantly undervalued. Cash is still King. Any buys I make
are done in very small amounts.

It's still too early to even think of loading up. On any significant bounce, I
have my list of stocks for sale and may even consider selling some of my recent
purchases for a quick gain.

